</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      name="url_search_iframe" 
      id="url_search_iframe"
      allowFullScreen="true"
      src="/url/search/https://kodi.softonic.com.br/android"></iframe> -->
</div>

<script>
    ARQUIVO.afterIframe();
  </script>

<h1 class="noprint"><i class="fa fa-circle-o-notch fa-spin noprint"></i></h1>
</div>

</body>
</html>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20190327081648mp_/https://free-pascal.softonic.com.br/mac" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }

    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20190325093522mp_/https://github.com/arquivo/pwa-technologies/wiki" target="_parent">
</iframe>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script> ARQUIVO.beforeIframe(); /*Load Arquivo specific code before iframe*/</script>
<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20180718142839mp_/https://burn.softonic.com.br/mac" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

  </script>

</div>

</body>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20091001103133mp_/http://www.opensource.org/" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/http://saber.sapo.pt/wiki/Opensource"></iframe> -->
</div>

  </script>

</div>

</body>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }

      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20170605175158mp_/http://plone.org/" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20150410134409mp_/http://www.opensource.org/" target="_parent">
