<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/https://www.coar-repositories.org/"></iframe> -->
</div>

  </script>

</div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          window.postMessage(message);

      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

  </script>

      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

        }

    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20200902224916mp_/http://www.acesso-aberto.pt/?fchange=d" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

                               "request_ts": "20190913192934",
                               "iframe": "#replay_iframe"});
ARQUIVO.updateInfo(wbinfo.capture_url, "20190913192934");
</script>
</link></meta></meta></head>

<!-- Overwriting pywb set_state function in order to properly update our toolbar when iframe changes-->
<script> ARQUIVO.beforeIframe(); /*Load Arquivo specific code before iframe*/</script>
<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20190913192934mp_/https://bibliosubject.iscte-iul.pt/sp4/subjects/guide.php?subject=acessoaberto" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }

        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

            return;

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          };

      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20170606111842mp_/https://www/eventos/8a-conferencia-luso-brasileira-de-acesso-aberto-confoa/" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

	if( language == 'EN'){
		document.write('<script type="text/javascript" language="JavaScript" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/static/properties/ConstantsEN.js"><\/script>');

		document.write('<script type="text/javascript" language="JavaScript" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/static/properties/ConstantsPT.js"><\/script>');

<script type="text/javascript">
var tokens = window.location.toString().split('/');
theURL = '';
var i;
for( i = 5; i<tokens.length; i ++){
	if(i == 5){
		theURL = tokens[i];
	}
	else{
		theURL= theURL + "/" + tokens[i];
	}
}

document.write('<div id="pageIsNotArchived"><a href="///?l='+ Content.language +'"><img src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/static/img/logo.svg" class="imgClass" /></a>');

document.write('<h2 align="center" class="notArchived">'+ Content.notArchived+'</h2>'); 

document.write('<div class="myButtonStyle text-center" >'+
               '	<a id="otherArchives" class="greyFont" role="button" onclick="">'+Content.otherArchives+
               '	</a>'+
               '</div></div>');

$('#otherArchives').on('click', function(e){

            /*gtag('event', 'ReplayBarFunctions', { "action": 'Search Other Archives Click', "label": 'http://arquivo.pt/'+_ts+'/'+_url } );*/
            uglipop({
              class:'modalReplay noprint', //styling class for Modal
              source:'html',
              content:'<h4 class="modalTitleComplete"><i class="fa fa-print" aria-hidden="true"></i> '+Content.otherArchives+'</h4><p class="modalparagraph last">'+Content.leavingArquivo+'</p>'+
                      '<div class="row"><a id="searchOtherArchives" onclick="gtag(\'event\', \'ReplayBarFunctions\', { "action":\'Search Other Archives Click\', "label": \'arquivo.pt/'+tokens[4]+'/'+theURL+'\' } );" class="col-xs-6 text-center leftAnchor modalOptions">OK</a><a id="cancelPopup" class="col-xs-6 text-center modalOptions">'+Content.cancel+'</a></div>'
            });
    /*Closing popup*/            
    $('#cancelPopup').on('click', function(e){
        gtag("event", 'Not Found', {
            "type": 'Other Archives Cancel', 
            "url": 'arquivo.pt/'+tokens[4]+'/'+theURL 
        } );
        $('#uglipop_content_fixed').fadeOut();
        $('#uglipop_overlay').fadeOut('fast');
    });
    /*Confirm searching other archives*/
    $('#searchOtherArchives').on('click', function(e){
        gtag("event", 'Not Found', {
            "type": 'Other Archives Confirm', 
            "url": 'arquivo.pt/'+tokens[4]+'/'+theURL 
        } );
        window.open('https://web.archive.org/web/'+tokens[4]+'/'+theURL);
        $('#uglipop_overlay').fadeOut('fast');
    });  

});

// hide replay option when on not archived page
window.parent.document.getElementById("replayMenuButton").style.display = "none";

</script>

    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }

      // Check sender origin to be trusted

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.

          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20170217161126mp_/http://alfinete2008.blogspot.pt/search/label/acesso%20aberto?updated-max=2011-04-19T07:45:00%2B01:00&amp;max-results=20&amp;start=20&amp;by-date=false" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
