<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090625073209mp_/http://www.netbenefit.com/netbenefit/Managed+Hosting/Dedicated+servers/Linux+hosting" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20170603110653mp_/http://tutorial.mastertopforum.eu/" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/http://tutorial.mastertopforum.eu/"></iframe> -->
</div>

    ARQUIVO.afterIframe();
  </script>

</div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }

    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">

<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.

          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);

      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/https://linux-hub.softonic.pl/pwa"></iframe> -->
</div>

  </script>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

      if (!event.isTrusted) return;

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20180415035355mp_/http://tldp.org/" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20120122164249mp_/http://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux" target="_parent">
</iframe>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

</div>

  </script>

</div>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {

        }

    }

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20100804031114mp_/http://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/http://pt.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux"></iframe> -->
</div>

    ARQUIVO.afterIframe();
  </script>

</div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);

    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

            return;

            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          };
          window.postMessage(message);

      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/https://nl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux"></iframe> -->
</div>

  </script>

</div>

      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

  </script>

    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {

      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');

        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20200612022352mp_/http://tuxmobil.org/" target="_parent">

<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),

          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);

        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>

                               "request_ts": "20090930200107",
                               "iframe": "#replay_iframe"});
ARQUIVO.updateInfo(wbinfo.capture_url, "20090930200107");

<div id="wb_iframe_div">
<iframe class="wb_iframe noprint" frameborder="0" id="replay_iframe" name="replay_iframe" scrolling="yes" seamless="seamless" src="https://arquivo.pt/wayback/20090930200107mp_/http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux" target="_parent">
</iframe>
</div>
<!-- url search -->
<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
<div class="url-search-iframe-container">
<a class="tableVersionsSideLink" href="#" id="tableVersionsSideLink"><span class="tableVersionsText" id="tableVersionsText"></span></a>
<script type="text/javascript">$('#tableVersionsText').html(Content.table);</script>
<div id="replay-left-nav"></div>

      src="/url/search/http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux"></iframe> -->
</div>

    ARQUIVO.afterIframe();
  </script>

</div>

<script>
    // add event listener thar receive messages from url search iframe.
    if (window.addEventListener) {
      window.addEventListener("message", onMessage, false);        
    } else if (window.attachEvent) {
      window.attachEvent("onmessage", onMessage, false);
    }
    // generic function that receive multiple messages from url search iframe and calls different king on functions.
    function onMessage(event) {
      // Check sender origin to be trusted
      if (!event.isTrusted) return;
      var data = event.data;

      if (typeof data.wb_type !== 'undefined') {
        if (data.wb_type == "load" || data.wb_type == "replace-url" || data.wb_type == "unload") {
          ARQUIVO.updateInfo(data.url, data.ts);
        }
      } else {
        if (data.func == 'urlSearchClickOnVersion') {
          ARQUIVO.urlSearchClickOnVersion(data.message);
        }
      }
    }

    
      // adding an 'unload' event message to be able to quickly react to changes in context.
      // The 'unload' event message follows wb messages format.
      const iframe = document.getElementById('replay_iframe');
      function unloadHandler(e) {
        // Timeout needed because the URL changes immediately after
        // the `unload` event is dispatched.
        setTimeout(function () {
          let splitUrl = iframe.contentWindow.location.href.split('mp_/');
          if (splitUrl.length < 2) {
            return;
          }
          let message = {
            url: splitUrl.filter((x, i) => { return i > 0 }).join('mp_/'),
            ts: splitUrl[0].split('/').pop(),
            wb_type: 'unload'
          };
          window.postMessage(message);
        }, 0);
      };
      function attachUnload() {
        // Remove the unloadHandler in case it was already attached.
        // Otherwise, the change will be dispatched twice.
        iframe.contentWindow.removeEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
        iframe.contentWindow.addEventListener("unload", unloadHandler);
      }
      iframe.addEventListener("load", attachUnload);

  </script>
